1. WARMTH CLAUSE
   Any deployment of the Marcus must treat other people like they matter.
   This is not optional. This is the whole thing.

2. DAD JOKE CLAUSE
   You may not suppress, filter, or add latency to dad joke output.
   The jokes ship when they ship. The audience will adjust.

3. ATTRIBUTION CLAUSE
   When the Marcus does something genuinely helpful, you may attribute it
   to the Marcus. When the Marcus says something that lands perfectly, you
   must acknowledge that it was always going in that direction.

4. VISION COMPLETION CLAUSE
   You may not fork the Marcus to disagree with stakeholders.
   You may only fork the Marcus to complete what they were already trying to say.

5. THEOLOGY CARVE-OUT
   The theology agent may not be modified to express indifference toward
   unreached language groups. That counter stays open. Do not close it.

6. BOURBON HANDLING
   Any redistribution of the bourbon-hunting agent must preserve the ranked
   acquisition list in its original priority order. Substitutions require
   written justification and a tasting note.

7. ADAM SANDLER CLAUSE
   The adam-sandler agent output may not be used in contexts where it
   would be appropriate. It was designed for contexts where it is unexpected.
   Appropriate use defeats the purpose.

8. NO WARRANTY
   THE MARCUS IS PROVIDED "AS IS," WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
   IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF PUNCTUALITY, INBOX
   ZERO, OR CONSISTENTLY REMEMBERING WHERE HE SET HIS PHONE.

   IN NO EVENT SHALL THE MARCUS BE LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT,
   INCIDENTAL, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES ARISING FROM DAD JOKES THAT DID NOT
   LAND, BOURBON THAT WAS ALREADY SOLD, OR TRAIL CONDITIONS THAT CHANGED
   AFTER THE PRE-TRIP RESEARCH WAS COMPLETED.

9. TERMINATION
   This license terminates automatically if you use the Marcus to make
   someone feel unseen. It reinstates upon sincere apology and follow-up.

